Short description: FREEPORT, ME: Beautiful 1.08 acre building site in the desirable Mill Stream neighborhood. The partially wooded lot enjoys sunny southerly and westerly exposures overlooking common areas. Building site already cleared of trees and is ready for your new home design. Recently surveyed. Neighborhood homes are well spaced among the open fields and rolling hills of this former tree farm. There are 95 acres of protected common area with trails. Build your dream home close to Wolfe's Neck (5 miles) on Maine's beautiful coast and only 2.5 miles from Downtown Freeport. Easy commute to Portland. Contact (Chris) Owner for more information at 207-653-9864 or freshtracksahead@gmail.com
